FEATURES             Location/Qualifiers
     protein_domain  1..116
                     /label="SpyCatcher"
                     /synonym="SpyCatcher001"
                     /synonym="Spy Catcher"
                     /note="116-aa protein partner of the SpyTag/SpyCatcher
                     covalent-conjugation system, engineered by splitting the
                     CnaB2 immunoglobulin-like collagen-adhesion domain of
                     Streptococcus pyogenes fibronectin-binding protein FbaB
                     into a protein fragment (SpyCatcher, contains the reactive
                     Lys31) and a 13-aa peptide (SpyTag, contains the reactive
                     Asp). On mixing with SpyTag, the side-chain amine of
                     SpyCatcher Lys31 spontaneously and irreversibly forms an
                     intermolecular isopeptide (amide) bond to SpyTag Asp7,
                     catalysed by SpyCatcher Glu77; the linkage resists boiling
                     in SDS and forces up to ~1 nN. As stored the domain begins
                     with a vector-derived Gly-Ala-Met (residues 24-139 of
                     AFD50637.1, the standard post-TEV-cleavage product) and is
                     fusable at a protein N- or C-terminus. Structural and
                     biochemical work shows the N-terminal ~23 and C-terminal ~9
                     residues are dispensable, defining a minimized 84-aa core
                     (original residues 21-104)."
                     /citation=[1]
